definition.value: An N(6')-acetylkanamycin derived from kanamycin B.
An isoquinoline substituted by a methyl group at position 3.
A ribonucleic acid that is ribosomal RNA (rRNA) in which one of the RNA bases is N(2)-methylguanine.
A nonaprenyl diphosphate where all C=C double bonds have (E)-configuration.
An alpha-tocopherol that has R,R,R configuration. The naturally occurring stereoisomer of alpha-tocopherol, it is found particularly in sunflower and olive oils.
